			title: "Fortress Found"
			icon: "minecraft:nether_brick"
			description: [
				"§6YUNG's Better Nether Fortresses§f replaces the vanilla Nether Fortress"
				"§fwith a large, multi-wing complex. If you've seen vanilla fortresses,"
				"§fforgot them — these are far larger and more dangerous."
				""
				"§eWhat's in a YUNG's Fortress:§r"
				"§7• §eBlaze Spawner rooms§7 — multiple, spread throughout the complex."
				"§7• §eWither Skeleton halls§7 — dense, narrow corridors. High Wither risk."
				"§7• §eLoot chest rooms§7 — locked rooms often behind hidden doors."
				"§7• §eCentral courtyard§7 — open-air arena with multiple spawners at once."
				""
				"§eFinding the Fortress:§r"
				"§7• They generate in §eNether Wastes§7 and §eCrimson Forest§7 biomes."
				"§7• Nature's Compass can search for the §eminecraft:nether_wastes§7 biome"
				"§7  if you need to relocate the original fortress direction."
				"§7• Fortresses often have §ebridge extensions§7 visible from a distance."
				""
				"§ePreparation:§r"
				"§7• §ePotion of Fire Resistance§7 — mandatory. Blaze fireballs are frequent."
				"§7• §eMilk Buckets§7 ×4 — for Wither Skeleton wither effect."
				"§7• §eFull Iron armor§7 minimum; §eDiamond§7 recommended."
				""
				"§a► Reach the main entrance of a YUNG's Nether Fortress. Mark done."
			]
			dependencies: ["000D000F"]
